hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The recessional velocity at emission is 
   $$\dot d_p(t_e)\;=\;\dot a(t_e)\,\chi\;=\;c\quad\Longrightarrow\quad \chi \;=\;\frac{c}{\dot a(t_e)}\,. $$

2. The comoving distance is 
   $$\chi \;=\;\int_{t_e}^{t_0}\frac{c\,dt}{a(t)}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad 
     \int_{t_e}^{t_0}\frac{dt}{a(t)}\;=\;\frac{1}{\dot a(t_e)}\,. $$

3. Change variables to redshift $z$, with $a=1/(1+z)$ and $dt=-dz/[(1+z)H(z)]$:
   $$\frac{dt}{a(t)} \;=\;-\frac{dz}{(1+z)H(z)}\;\frac{1}{a(t)}\;=\;-\frac{dz}{H(z)}\,. $$
   Hence
   $$\int_{t_e}^{t_0}\frac{dt}{a(t)}
     =\int_{z_e}^{0}\!-\frac{dz}{H(z)}
     =\int_{0}^{z_e}\frac{dz}{H(z)}
     =\frac{1}{\dot a(t_e)}\,. $$

4. Using $\dot a(t_e)=H(z_e)\,a(t_e)=H(z_e)/(1+z_e)$ gives
   $$\int_{0}^{z_e}\frac{dz}{H(z)}
     \;=\;\frac{1+z_e}{H(z_e)}\,. $$

5. For domain walls $w=-\tfrac23$, 
   $$H(z)=H_0(1+z)^{\frac12}\,. $$
   Thus
   $$\int_{0}^{z_e}\frac{dz}{H_0\sqrt{1+z}}
     =\frac{1+z_e}{H_0\sqrt{1+z_e}}
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     \int_{0}^{z_e}\frac{dz}{\sqrt{1+z}}
     =\frac{1+z_e}{\sqrt{1+z_e}}\,. $$

6. Compute the integral:
   $$\int_{0}^{z_e}(1+z)^{-\frac12}dz
     =2\bigl[\sqrt{1+z}\bigr]_{0}^{z_e}
     =2\bigl(\sqrt{1+z_e}-1\bigr)\,. $$
   The equation becomes
   $$2(\sqrt{1+z_e}-1)=\frac{1+z_e}{\sqrt{1+z_e}}\,. $$
   Set $S=\sqrt{1+z_e}$, then $2(S-1)=S\;\Rightarrow\;S=2\;\Rightarrow\;1+z_e=4\;\Rightarrow\;z_e=3\,. $
